reviews.review_text: smokin!!! smokin!!! what great form the band was in!!
Space is fun Like most audience recordings it gets better as the show progresses, mahalo Tapers!

Vibey summer show This is not just a great show, but a great recording. It's an example of when an AUD really shines, even over a SBD. While there are minor flaws in the sound quality, they're more than made up for by the sound of the crowd, the natural reverb of the venue, etc. You feel like you're hanging out on a warm July day with friends.

The show starts with a somewhat laid-back, but not lazy first set. The energy slowly builds and then continues for a classic second set: Deal, Samson, Ship of Fools, Estimated > Eyes, which transitions into a wild bass/drums jam, continuing with a beautiful Wharf Rat, and some fun ones to finish off with a party.

One of my favorite shows!
